.SH NAME
gen-ng \- program to generate radio transmission test signals
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-ng
.RI [ options ]\ output_file
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBgen-ng\fP software generates test signals for various digital transmission
modes commonly found on VHF/UHF radio. It is the companion tool to
\fBmultimon-ng\fP and can be used to create test files for decoder validation.
.PP
The output is 16-bit signed PCM audio at 22050 Hz sample rate, which can be
fed directly to multimon-ng for testing or converted to other formats using
tools like sox.
.PP
Currently, the following modes are supported:
.PP
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
DTMF (Dual Tone Multi Frequency)
.IP \(bu 4
ZVEI (selective calling)
.IP \(bu 4
UART (serial data)
.IP \(bu 4
HDLC (High-Level Data Link Control packets)
.IP \(bu 4
CLIP FSK (Caller ID)
.IP \(bu 4
Sine wave (test tone)
.IP \(bu 4
FLEX (paging protocol at 1600 baud 2-FSK)
.IP \(bu 4
POCSAG (paging protocol at 512, 1200, or 2400 baud)
.IP \(bu 4
Scope text (waveforms for SDL_SCOPE display)
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B  \-t <type>
Output file type. Use 'raw' for direct output or any other type supported by sox
(wav, flac, mp3, etc.). Types other than raw require sox to be installed.
.TP
.B  \-a <ampl>
Set signal amplitude (default: 16384).
.TP
.B  \-d <string>
Generate DTMF tones for the given digit string.
Valid characters: 0-9, A-D, *, #.
.TP
.B  \-z <string>
Generate ZVEI selective call tones for the given digit string.
.TP
.B  \-s <freq>
Generate a sine wave at the specified frequency in Hz.
.TP
.B  \-u <text>
Generate UART-encoded serial data containing the specified text.
.TP
.B  \-p <text>
Generate an HDLC packet containing the specified text.
.TP
.B  \-c <string>
Generate CLIP FSK (Caller ID) data.
.TP
.B  \-f <message>
Generate a FLEX pager message. The message is encoded as alphanumeric text.
.TP
.B  \-F <capcode>
Set the FLEX pager address/capcode (default: 1234567).
Must be in the range 1 to 2097151.
.TP
.B  \-e <0-3>
Inject bit errors into FLEX or POCSAG codewords for BCH error correction testing.
0 = no errors, 1 = one-bit errors, 2 = two-bit errors (correctable),
3 = three-bit errors (uncorrectable, for negative testing).
This option must follow \-f (FLEX) or \-P (POCSAG).
.TP
.B  \-P <message>
Generate a POCSAG pager message. By default, the message is encoded as
alphanumeric text (7-bit ASCII). Use \-N for numeric mode.
.TP
.B  \-A <address>
Set the POCSAG pager address/capcode (default: 1234567).
Must be in the range 0 to 2097151.
.TP
.B  \-B <baud>
Set the POCSAG baud rate: 512, 1200, or 2400 (default: 1200).
.TP
.B  \-N
Use POCSAG numeric mode (function 0) instead of alphanumeric mode.
Valid numeric characters: 0-9, space, hyphen (-), period (.), U.
.TP
.B  \-I
Generate POCSAG signal with inverted polarity. Use this to test the decoder's
auto-detection of inverted signals.
.TP
.B  \-S <text>
Generate waveforms that render readable text on the SDL_SCOPE display.
Uses a 5x7 bitmap font.
.TP
.B  \-h
Print help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate a DTMF tone sequence and decode it:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -d "123456" /tmp/dtmf.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a DTMF /tmp/dtmf.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a FLEX pager message:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -f "Hello World" -F 12345 /tmp/flex.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a FLEX /tmp/flex.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a FLEX message with 2-bit errors to test BCH correction:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -f "Test" -F 54321 -e 2 /tmp/flex_err.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a FLEX /tmp/flex_err.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a POCSAG alphanumeric message at 1200 baud:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -P "Meeting at 3pm" -A 67890 /tmp/pocsag.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a POCSAG1200 /tmp/pocsag.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a POCSAG numeric message at 512 baud:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -P "1234567890" -N -A 11111 -B 512 /tmp/pocsag.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a POCSAG512 /tmp/pocsag.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a POCSAG message with 2-bit errors to test BCH correction:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -P "Test" -A 54321 -e 2 /tmp/pocsag_err.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a POCSAG1200 /tmp/pocsag_err.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a POCSAG message with inverted polarity:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -P "Inverted test" -A 12345 -I /tmp/pocsag_inv.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a POCSAG1200 /tmp/pocsag_inv.raw
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate a WAV file (requires sox):
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t wav -f "Pager test" -F 99999 /tmp/flex.wav
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate text for the SDL_SCOPE display:
.RS
.nf
gen-ng -t raw -S "HELLO" /tmp/scope.raw
multimon-ng -t raw -a SDL_SCOPE /tmp/scope.raw
.fi
.RE
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
The raw output format is 16-bit signed little-endian PCM at 22050 Hz sample rate,
mono channel. This is the same format expected by multimon-ng with the \-t raw option.
